# PopAlpha catalog bundle (.papb) — 37MB binary built from the SigLIP-2
# catalog in Supabase by `cog/siglip-features/build_catalog_bundle.py`.
#
# 2026-05-05: previously gitignored (intent: download on premium
# activation from Supabase Storage). Real-device measurements showed
# the cold-launch HEAD+download path at ~6.5s, blocking the offline
# scanner during the user's first scan. The catalog manager now uses
# stale-while-revalidate: load the bundled .papb immediately, kick off
# a background ETag check, atomic-swap a newer copy into the cache if
# one exists. To make that work in CI / TestFlight builds, the .papb
# itself has to be committed — the previous "regenerate locally" path
# only worked on dev machines.
#
# So the .papb is intentionally tracked now. Regenerate with:
#
#   cd cog/siglip-features
#   source venv/bin/activate
#   python build_catalog_bundle.py --output siglip2_catalog_v1.papb --quantize-fp16
#   python upload_catalog_bundle.py --input siglip2_catalog_v1.papb
#   cp siglip2_catalog_v1.papb \
#     ../../ios/Sources/Features/Scanner/Resources/Catalog/
#
# The upload step keeps Supabase Storage in sync with the committed
# binary so background revalidation picks up the same bake. Both have
# to move together — if you only re-bake locally, CI builds drift from
# what users get over the air.
